race.comment: LOVELY LUCY (1) finds it hard to win with just one success from 19 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when fifth over 905m at this track, beaten 4 lengths. Best figures measure up nicely. Makes plenty of appeal. CAIRNHILL (2) has switched yards since scoring by 2.5 lengths at this track over 905m on September 6. Has ability and should be right in the finish. COUSHATTA CUTIE (4) missed the placings two runs back then was always well out of her ground last start when 28 lengths away in fifth over 1207m at Colonial Downs. Has the class to figure prominently. TIDBIT (8) has been out of the winner's list for a long time, last start finishing eighth at this track (Dirt) over 1408m. Nicely placed to turn things around.
